WEBVTT

00:05.772 --> 00:07.307
CLYDE: <i>13 Bannerman Road</i>
<i>is where</i>
<i>Sarah Jane Smith lives</i>

00:07.374 --> 00:10.677
<i>and it's home to things</i>
<i>way beyond your imagination.</i>

00:10.744 --> 00:14.147
<i>There's an extraterrestrial,</i>
<i>super computer in the wall,</i>

00:14.214 --> 00:17.450
<i>her son, a genetically</i>
<i>engineered boy genius,</i>

00:17.517 --> 00:20.286
<i>a school girl investigator</i>
<i>across the road</i>

00:20.353 --> 00:24.023
<i>and a whole universe</i>
<i>of adventure right here</i>
<i>on the doorstep.</i>

00:31.131 --> 00:32.598
-Ready?
-Always.

00:39.139 --> 00:41.841
LUKE: <i>Our world has always</i>
<i>been full of nightmares.</i>

00:41.908 --> 00:45.145
<i>Creatures and aliens</i>
<i>who want to destroy us.</i>

00:45.211 --> 00:47.480
<i>But we've always</i>
<i>been protected.</i>

00:47.547 --> 00:50.850
<i>The Doctor.</i>
<i>His friends. My mum.</i>

00:52.152 --> 00:53.119
<i>But tonight...</i>

00:55.355 --> 00:57.457
<i>Tonight I don't think</i>
<i>anyone can save us.</i>

00:59.559 --> 01:02.429
The world's going to end,
and it's my fault.

01:04.897 --> 01:07.667
Because he's coming for me,
you see?

01:07.734 --> 01:11.404
He's been waiting
for me for years.
And this week, he...

01:11.471 --> 01:12.939
(MANIACAL LAUGHING)

01:15.341 --> 01:16.476
I can hear him.

01:18.978 --> 01:23.149
He's coming.
So, if you're watching,
just keep watching.

01:23.216 --> 01:25.652
<i>-Because...</i>
-THE NIGHTMARE MAN: <i>Lukey boy!</i>

01:28.721 --> 01:30.757
<i>He's The Nightmare Man.</i>

01:30.824 --> 01:32.091
<i>And I can't stop him.</i>

01:32.926 --> 01:34.661
<i>Mum, I'm sorry.</i>

01:55.114 --> 01:58.084
-Mum. Something's happened.
-Hmm?

01:58.151 --> 02:00.520
At school.
Mr Chandra called me
into his office because

02:00.587 --> 02:02.522
he thinks I should take
my A-levels in June.

02:02.589 --> 02:03.623
I mean...

02:03.690 --> 02:06.025
Well, you've
just started sixth form.

02:06.092 --> 02:10.363
I know, but
I'm clever, aren't I?

02:10.430 --> 02:12.932
It's why he thinks
I could get into Oxford.

02:12.999 --> 02:14.868
He says I could go to
university a year early.

02:16.469 --> 02:18.371
Mum?

02:18.438 --> 02:20.940
And you think now's the time
to be telling me this?

02:21.808 --> 02:24.744
<i>Bomb activation initiated.</i>

02:24.811 --> 02:27.547
<i>Bomb activation initiated.</i>

02:27.614 --> 02:29.849
<i>Bomb activation initiated.</i>

02:33.386 --> 02:34.954
SLITHEEN: Goodbye, Miss Smith!

02:35.021 --> 02:37.123
My ship is ready to go.

02:37.190 --> 02:40.360
I'd offer you a lift,
but you're all tied up.

02:40.426 --> 02:41.628
(BEEPING)

02:41.694 --> 02:43.630
RANI: K9! Stop the bomb!

02:43.696 --> 02:45.932
-K9: <i>Affirmative!</i>
-You escaped?

02:45.999 --> 02:48.501
K9: <i>Deactivating timer</i>
<i>mechanism, Mistress.</i>

02:48.568 --> 02:49.869
No!

02:49.936 --> 02:51.404
We warned you
but you wouldn't listen!

02:51.471 --> 02:54.541
You think you can stop me
with a bucket?

02:54.607 --> 02:55.975
A bucket full of vinegar.

02:58.811 --> 03:00.480
-Oh.
-(GURGLING)

03:02.382 --> 03:04.050
-Bum!
-Not again.

03:10.256 --> 03:12.325
(BEEPING)

03:12.392 --> 03:14.627
<i>Bomb neutralized, Mistress!</i>

03:18.831 --> 03:21.868
LUKE: Well, Mum? Oxford?

03:21.935 --> 03:24.871
I think you need to do
what's right for you.

03:26.472 --> 03:27.840
So, yes, Luke.

03:27.907 --> 03:29.075
I think you should go.

03:35.415 --> 03:37.250
(CROWD CHATTERING)

03:37.317 --> 03:39.719
I don't get why he wants
to go to uni anyway.

03:39.786 --> 03:42.555
We've got K9 and
Mr Smith. He could learn
everything from them.

03:42.622 --> 03:45.491
But he's got to meet
new people, do new things.

03:45.558 --> 03:47.860
Don't you want to
see the world?

03:47.927 --> 03:50.163
I've seen it. No space.

03:50.229 --> 03:51.464
(CHUCKLES)

03:51.531 --> 03:52.799
Here he is.

03:54.334 --> 03:55.435
Mum.

03:57.704 --> 04:00.173
-Four A-stars.
-Yeah!

04:00.239 --> 04:02.675
Well done, honey!
Oh, I'm so proud.

04:02.742 --> 04:05.111
-Come here, you, well done.
-Thank you.

04:05.178 --> 04:06.713
Never doubted you, man.

04:06.779 --> 04:08.247
(SIGHS) So...

04:08.314 --> 04:09.983
I'm going to university!

04:10.049 --> 04:11.417
I'm going to Oxford!

04:12.518 --> 04:14.220
I was so happy.

04:14.287 --> 04:15.989
Everything was going
to be fantastic.

04:16.990 --> 04:18.423
<i>But...</i>

04:18.491 --> 04:19.692
<i>But I was scared.</i>

04:21.094 --> 04:23.129
<i>It started back then, but</i>

04:23.196 --> 04:25.531
<i>this week,</i>
<i>I just got really scared.</i>

04:30.269 --> 04:31.871
<i>(BULLETPROOF</i> PLAYING ON RADIO)

04:56.396 --> 04:57.864
MR SMITH: <i>Initiating scan.</i>

04:59.232 --> 05:01.034
Oh, I was just
going to call you.

05:01.100 --> 05:04.070
I thought we'd have
scrambled eggs.

05:04.837 --> 05:06.372
I guess I should watch.

05:06.439 --> 05:08.741
This time next week I'll be
making my own breakfast.

05:08.808 --> 05:10.977
<i>Alien object of</i>
<i>Alphamatraxin origin.</i>

05:12.612 --> 05:13.880
I just saw Rani.

05:15.314 --> 05:17.850
Oh, first day back at school,
isn't it?

05:17.917 --> 05:19.852
-It must seem strange
not being with them.
-Yeah.

05:22.055 --> 05:24.190
Mum, have I made
the right choice?

05:24.257 --> 05:25.992
Of course you have.

05:26.059 --> 05:28.561
Remember your first day
at Park Vale?
You were terrified.

05:28.628 --> 05:29.929
That turned out all right.

05:30.129 --> 05:32.532
-We were attacked by Slitheen.
-Yeah, apart from that.

05:32.598 --> 05:35.835
-They turned the sun off.
-Yeah, and apart from that.

05:35.902 --> 05:38.504
Listen, Luke, you're allowed
to be worried.

05:38.571 --> 05:39.872
You're only human.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.109
Yeah.

05:45.678 --> 05:47.980
Are you really going to
make scrambled egg?

05:48.047 --> 05:50.483
Do you remember
what happened last time?

05:50.550 --> 05:53.052
I think I can manage,
thank you.

05:54.554 --> 05:57.724
"Mum just set the kitchen
on fire again.

05:57.790 --> 06:00.159
-"Are you coming
round tonight?"
-Luke?

06:00.226 --> 06:01.127
Yeah!

06:03.329 --> 06:05.631
-What, you're not going
to text back?
-Yeah, later.

06:08.134 --> 06:10.670
He should be here.
He should be here

06:10.737 --> 06:14.140
-boring us with facts
about dead kings and...
-(LAUGHING)

06:14.207 --> 06:16.976
-...space and dinosaurs.
-I know.

06:18.377 --> 06:22.148
Four days, and then that's it.
No more Luke.

06:22.215 --> 06:25.918
We've got these.
And he'll be home for holidays
and Christmas and...

06:27.653 --> 06:29.555
What, so you're going
to see him later?

06:31.591 --> 06:34.193
When my dad went,
he just went.

06:34.260 --> 06:36.596
Disappeared overnight.

06:36.662 --> 06:39.132
Luke needs to get used to
us not being around.

06:40.466 --> 06:41.868
Come on.

06:46.539 --> 06:48.608
I got these from Gita.

06:48.674 --> 06:50.910
You're lucky,
she wanted to help.

06:50.977 --> 06:54.080
Oh! You've made a start.
Not bad.

06:54.147 --> 06:56.482
Do you know?
I thought we'd get you
some new clothes.

06:56.549 --> 06:59.085
I don't know what's in
but Rani can help,

06:59.152 --> 07:01.921
and we'll get you
looking all cool.

07:01.988 --> 07:04.791
Oh! Is "cool" the right word?

07:04.857 --> 07:06.392
Is "cool" cool?

07:06.459 --> 07:07.860
-(CHUCKLES)
-Yeah.

07:10.797 --> 07:13.633
-Has he called you back?
-No.

07:13.699 --> 07:17.003
Oh, he's probably just sad.

07:17.069 --> 07:19.105
(SIGHS)

07:19.172 --> 07:22.742
Listen, I know what'll
cheer you up. Come on!

07:30.616 --> 07:32.718
Ta-da!

07:32.785 --> 07:34.821
It's your old car.

07:34.887 --> 07:37.456
-Not anymore.
-You're giving it to me?

07:40.259 --> 07:43.362
I've had it done up.
MOT, everything.

07:43.429 --> 07:45.698
You don't want
your mum driving you to uni.

07:47.033 --> 07:49.635
Come on, get in!
See how it feels!

07:53.472 --> 07:54.707
So?

07:55.975 --> 07:57.610
So why don't I
just drive off now?

07:59.412 --> 08:02.048
-What?
-Are you even
going to miss me?

08:04.183 --> 08:06.452
You want me to pack
and get new clothes,

08:06.519 --> 08:08.621
and it's like
you can't wait for me to go.

08:11.190 --> 08:12.091
(SIGHS)

08:12.892 --> 08:13.993
Oh!

08:23.636 --> 08:24.770
Listen.

08:24.837 --> 08:26.806
For years, I was alone.

08:26.873 --> 08:28.875
Just K9 and me.

08:30.610 --> 08:31.811
And... Uh...

08:32.778 --> 08:34.614
You gave me my life back.

08:35.914 --> 08:37.850
You gave me something real
to live for.

08:41.921 --> 08:44.557
I'm terrified of what's
going to happen when you go.

08:44.624 --> 08:45.658
(WEEPING)

08:46.826 --> 08:47.894
I'm so scared.

08:49.862 --> 08:51.998
-Why?
-Because

08:53.633 --> 08:54.934
it feels like I'm losing you.

08:59.639 --> 09:01.407
Everything's changing so fast.

09:02.108 --> 09:02.909
I know.

09:05.278 --> 09:08.180
But whatever happens,
this is your home.

09:08.247 --> 09:11.050
Your friends are here,
I'm here.

09:11.117 --> 09:13.786
And I'll always
be here for you.

09:13.853 --> 09:16.155
Well, of course,
I'm going to miss you.

09:18.925 --> 09:19.892
(SIGHS)

09:25.798 --> 09:27.066
(DISTANT MANIACAL LAUGHING)

09:35.875 --> 09:36.876
Uh!

09:38.077 --> 09:39.712
(DISTANT MANIACAL LAUGHING)

09:41.147 --> 09:42.248
K9: <i>Mistress?</i>

09:42.315 --> 09:43.983
(SARAH JANE LAUGHING)

09:44.050 --> 09:45.952
SARAH JANE: No, no.
I shouldn't laugh.

09:46.018 --> 09:49.722
Well, the thing is,
I'll miss him a bit.
But he's not really my son.

09:49.789 --> 09:53.159
<i>-Master Luke was</i>
<i>created by the Bane.</i>
-Exactly.

09:53.225 --> 09:54.627
And, well, yeah...

09:54.694 --> 09:56.929
He's good for
doing the crossword

09:56.996 --> 10:00.566
and emptying the bins,
but, oh, he was going
on earlier, K9.

10:00.633 --> 10:04.403
"Will you miss me?" I was
thinking, "Oh, for goodness'
sake, grow up!

10:04.470 --> 10:07.406
"And you know what? Actually,
I'm not going to miss you.
I don't really like you.

10:07.473 --> 10:09.809
"But once you started
living here,
I was stuck with you."

10:09.875 --> 10:11.944
<i>He will be gone soon.</i>

10:12.011 --> 10:14.046
Oh, K9, I can't wait.

10:14.113 --> 10:17.083
Luke was the biggest mistake
of my life!

10:17.149 --> 10:18.451
(GASPS)

10:22.688 --> 10:24.390
(DISTANT MANIACAL LAUGHING)

10:31.130 --> 10:36.102
Ah! Hi, Rani. Ah! Handbag.

10:36.168 --> 10:38.671
-She freaking out much?
-No, she's fine.

10:38.738 --> 10:40.773
(LAUGHING) And you?

10:42.475 --> 10:44.310
Luke.

10:44.377 --> 10:46.212
I had a nightmare last night.

10:46.278 --> 10:47.913
What? I thought you
couldn't dream.

10:47.980 --> 10:50.916
Neither did I.
The Bane didn't include it in
my genetic makeup.

10:51.717 --> 10:52.952
You told your mum?

10:53.953 --> 10:56.088
This is huge.

10:56.155 --> 10:59.158
It's just a dream.
Everybody has them,
don't they?

10:59.225 --> 11:02.228
Yeah. I suppose it must be
because you're leaving home.

11:02.294 --> 11:05.131
You know, everything's a
bit intense and that's just

11:05.197 --> 11:06.699
activated the dream switch.

11:07.700 --> 11:10.403
You're growing up,
getting old.

11:10.469 --> 11:13.272
I'm growing up
so I start having nightmares?
Great!

11:13.339 --> 11:17.243
Yep, and the rest of
us get spots.
I wouldn't worry about it.

11:17.309 --> 11:20.079
You've not told Clyde,
have you?
He'll only take the mick.

11:20.146 --> 11:21.947
I haven't seen him.
He's been busy.

11:24.950 --> 11:26.252
Clyde.

11:26.318 --> 11:27.753
I saw Luke this morning.

11:27.820 --> 11:30.089
He says he hasn't
see you in a few days.

11:30.156 --> 11:32.158
-Do you fancy
going round later?
-I've got football.

11:32.224 --> 11:34.193
-Oh, don't be like this.
-Like what?

11:34.260 --> 11:36.529
Your best mate's going away
on Friday. Don't pretend
you're not bothered.

11:36.595 --> 11:39.398
What am I supposed to do?
Start crying and then beg him
to stay?

11:39.465 --> 11:41.500
-No, we should be
happy for him!
-I am!

11:41.567 --> 11:42.868
-Tell him that!
-Maybe I will!

11:42.935 --> 11:43.869
-Good!
-Good!

11:46.238 --> 11:48.407
-(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)
-(CLEARS THROAT)

11:48.474 --> 11:50.109
-I actually have
to be in there.
-Oh, right, yeah.

12:02.421 --> 12:03.589
Night, Mum.

12:03.656 --> 12:04.790
SARAH JANE: Night!

12:05.891 --> 12:07.593
(DISTANT MANIACAL LAUGHING)

12:10.863 --> 12:11.997
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

12:20.072 --> 12:24.410
-Lukey boy!
What are you doing here?
-I don't know.

12:24.477 --> 12:27.746
I thought you were
the big man,
heading off to university?

12:27.813 --> 12:29.548
-It's not fair, really, is it?
-What isn't?

12:29.615 --> 12:33.119
-You. Your brain's not normal.
-Aw, is Rani jealous?

12:33.185 --> 12:37.823
I'm working so hard to get
out of here and he does
it all a year early.

12:37.890 --> 12:39.859
-He's just showing off.
-That isn't how it is.

12:39.925 --> 12:43.596
-You act like...
-BOTH: "Oh, I'm so sweet
and I'm so scared."

12:43.662 --> 12:45.598
-But you're just a freak.
-Super geek.

12:45.664 --> 12:46.999
-Alien freak.
-Ooh.

12:49.235 --> 12:50.870
Did someone say aliens?

12:50.936 --> 12:52.872
It's okay, Sarah Jane.
We'll still be here.

12:52.938 --> 12:56.342
-Yeah, we'll help you stop
the aliens.
-I'll be coming back.

12:56.408 --> 12:57.943
Who says we want you back?

13:00.980 --> 13:02.548
(DOOR CREAKING)

13:07.553 --> 13:08.888
MAN: <i>Luke...</i>

13:10.022 --> 13:11.190
Who are you?

13:11.257 --> 13:13.726
<i>I'm coming for you.</i>

13:13.792 --> 13:16.595
Who are you? Where am I?

13:16.662 --> 13:18.631
It's just a dream.

13:19.865 --> 13:23.602
I know.
I know this isn't real.

13:23.669 --> 13:26.205
But it isn't just a dream.
It can't be.

13:26.272 --> 13:28.407
MAN: <i>Poor little Lukey.</i>

13:35.447 --> 13:37.283
Who are you?

13:37.349 --> 13:41.120
MAN:
<i>I live in your nightmares.</i>

13:41.187 --> 13:44.390
<i>I feed on them. Oh...</i>

13:44.456 --> 13:46.859
<i>And yours are just</i>

13:48.194 --> 13:50.429
<i>beautiful.</i>

13:54.633 --> 13:55.901
(DOOR CREAKING)

13:59.438 --> 14:00.372
(SLAMMING)

14:18.924 --> 14:19.992
Morning.

14:22.995 --> 14:24.730
What's up?

14:24.797 --> 14:26.165
I didn't get much sleep.

14:26.232 --> 14:28.100
-I had a nightmare.
-What?

14:28.167 --> 14:29.568
I had one Monday as well.

14:30.502 --> 14:32.871
Right! Mr Smith, I need you.

14:36.675 --> 14:40.846
Mum, I'm sure it's nothing.
I'm just a bit
scared about Friday.

14:40.913 --> 14:42.648
<i>How can I help you,</i>
<i>Sarah Jane?</i>

14:42.715 --> 14:45.651
Scan Luke.
He's been having dreams.

14:45.718 --> 14:47.820
<i>I thought Luke didn't dream.</i>

14:47.886 --> 14:49.788
That's why I'm
asking you to scan him.

14:49.855 --> 14:53.592
Do you require everything
to be pointed out to you,
Mr Smith?

14:57.696 --> 14:59.131
Well?

14:59.198 --> 15:01.166
<i>Your anxiety</i>
<i>levels are increased,</i>

15:01.233 --> 15:04.603
<i>which is to be expected,</i>
<i>but I can't detect</i>
<i>any abnormalities.</i>

15:04.670 --> 15:06.705
So, I'm fine?

15:06.772 --> 15:09.808
Well, perhaps I should have
someone else look you over?

15:09.875 --> 15:11.477
Mum, I'm fine.

15:11.543 --> 15:13.479
Mr Smith said I'm fine.

15:13.545 --> 15:17.283
-I'm a big boy now.
-Oh, sorry.

15:17.349 --> 15:18.717
-(MOBILE BEEPS)
-How will I cope when
you're gone?

15:18.784 --> 15:21.320
I'm going to be
calling you and...

15:21.387 --> 15:24.390
I'll just talk to myself then.

15:24.456 --> 15:25.991
It's Clyde.
He wants to meet up.

15:26.058 --> 15:28.360
-What, now?
-This afternoon, in school.

15:28.427 --> 15:30.462
Yes, well, make sure you do
some packing before...

15:30.529 --> 15:31.664
Okay, Mum.

15:32.464 --> 15:33.832
Oh!

15:45.911 --> 15:46.879
Hello?

15:48.180 --> 15:50.382
ALL: Surprise!

15:52.618 --> 15:54.386
Did you do this?

15:54.453 --> 15:56.689
You're my best mate. As if I'd
let you leave without a party.

15:56.755 --> 16:00.926
-You hear me?
It's time to party!
-(ALL CHEERING)

16:01.126 --> 16:02.861
<i>(UNTOUCHABLE</i> PLAYING)

16:31.824 --> 16:33.025
(CHUCKLES)

16:33.092 --> 16:34.993
-So, you okay?
-Yeah.

16:35.694 --> 16:36.829
Okay!

16:36.895 --> 16:38.597
Good.

16:38.664 --> 16:41.233
It's just...
I'm not used to
this sort of thing.

16:41.300 --> 16:42.434
Me neither.

16:43.369 --> 16:44.937
So, we're cool?

16:45.137 --> 16:48.440
-We're always cool.
-Cool.

16:48.507 --> 16:50.743
And you don't want, like,
a hug or anything?

16:53.812 --> 16:56.348
So was this your idea?

16:56.415 --> 16:58.851
Yeah. Yeah, with a little
nudge from you-know-who.

17:03.422 --> 17:05.924
-She's cool, isn't she?
-Yeah. Yeah.

17:05.991 --> 17:08.560
-You should go
and dance with her.
-What?

17:08.627 --> 17:10.462
What's that supposed to mean?

17:10.529 --> 17:11.829
Why would I want to dance
with Rani? I don't want
to dance with...

17:11.896 --> 17:13.432
Rani?

17:13.499 --> 17:15.467
Clyde wants to show
you his moves!

17:20.571 --> 17:22.107
(CHUCKLES)

17:27.413 --> 17:29.848
RANI: Whoo!

17:49.902 --> 17:50.869
Clyde?

17:52.938 --> 17:53.872
Rani?

18:03.582 --> 18:06.151
Hello, Luke!

18:06.218 --> 18:09.621
-Who are you?
-I'm The Nightmare Man.

18:10.489 --> 18:13.358
You belong to me.

18:13.425 --> 18:15.928
But what are you doing here?
You're in the real world.

18:27.773 --> 18:30.642
-I've got to wake up.
-Your dreams are giving me

18:30.709 --> 18:34.246
such power over you, Luke.

18:34.313 --> 18:35.914
You can't say my name.

18:35.981 --> 18:40.619
You can't tell
anyone about me.

18:40.686 --> 18:42.988
I'm in your head, Luke.

18:45.290 --> 18:46.925
Your fear is

18:49.094 --> 18:50.496
delicious!

18:52.197 --> 18:53.899
Oi, oi. Have you been asleep?

18:55.467 --> 18:56.935
I don't know.

18:57.135 --> 18:58.904
-Ooh, is that more cake?
-Where?

19:02.608 --> 19:04.109
Did you have
another nightmare?

19:05.344 --> 19:07.613
Yeah. There was this...

19:09.615 --> 19:10.749
This...

19:13.151 --> 19:14.353
I can't say it.

19:14.419 --> 19:16.522
You're really scared,
aren't you?

19:16.588 --> 19:19.591
Look, it's just a nightmare
because you're stressed
out about Friday.

19:19.658 --> 19:21.326
You're going to be okay.

19:21.393 --> 19:23.662
-But I...
-Come on. Let's show Clyde
how it's done.

19:38.076 --> 19:39.845
THE NIGHTMARE MAN:
<i>You can't say my name,</i>

19:39.912 --> 19:44.283
<i>you can't tell</i>
<i>anyone about me.</i>

19:44.349 --> 19:46.852
<i>I'm in your head, Luke.</i>

19:47.886 --> 19:49.421
(THE NIGHTMARE MAN LAUGHS)

20:01.633 --> 20:03.502
And this is the attic.

20:08.373 --> 20:10.609
CLYDE: Mr. Smith? I need you!

20:15.847 --> 20:17.616
-Wow.
-(LAUGHING)

20:18.850 --> 20:20.352
Mum?

20:20.419 --> 20:23.155
What do you think, Josh?
Do you like it?

20:23.221 --> 20:26.425
-Aw, he's so sweet.
-He's my new baby boy.

20:26.491 --> 20:29.261
<i>Sarah Jane, I'm receiving</i>
<i>a call from Luke.</i>

20:29.328 --> 20:31.863
Oh, take a message.
I've got Josh now.

20:35.767 --> 20:38.637
THE NIGHTMARE MAN: <i>Have they</i>
<i>forgotten you already?</i>

20:45.877 --> 20:47.946
Clyde? Rani?

20:48.013 --> 20:50.082
Photos of Luke...

20:50.148 --> 20:53.652
-Gone.
-His old school
books... Gone.

20:53.719 --> 20:55.887
-You getting rid
of that as well?
-Yeah.

20:56.888 --> 20:58.390
It's all over, isn't it?

21:02.327 --> 21:03.428
No!

21:04.730 --> 21:06.064
(MANIACAL LAUGHING)

21:19.745 --> 21:20.846
SARAH JANE: Come on, in we go.

21:24.650 --> 21:26.752
LUKE: Clyde! Rani!

21:26.818 --> 21:28.620
(THE NIGHTMARE MAN LAUGHING)

21:32.691 --> 21:34.259
What are you?

21:34.326 --> 21:36.261
What do you want?

21:36.328 --> 21:37.729
What do you want?

21:38.864 --> 21:39.865
Life.

21:41.700 --> 21:43.368
Your nightmares,

21:43.435 --> 21:46.705
your fear,
they're giving me such power.

21:46.772 --> 21:50.742
One more little
nightmare from you,

21:50.809 --> 21:52.577
and I'll be in

21:53.412 --> 21:55.347
your world.

21:55.414 --> 21:57.249
-You can't!
-(LAUGHING)

21:57.315 --> 22:00.318
I'll send everyone
into an eternal sleep,

22:00.385 --> 22:04.156
a whole world of nightmares
for me to feed upon.

22:04.222 --> 22:07.125
And I'll grow stronger
and stronger. Oh, ho, ho!

22:07.192 --> 22:09.528
It's going to be so good.
Ho, ho!

22:09.594 --> 22:12.931
And it's all because
of you, Lukey.

22:15.434 --> 22:17.803
-Where are you from?
-What?

22:17.869 --> 22:19.971
What planet are you from?

22:20.038 --> 22:23.008
I'm from nowhere.
I'm from everywhere.

22:23.075 --> 22:25.477
You're just an alien,
and I've stopped
aliens before.

22:25.544 --> 22:27.746
But wouldn't it be terrifying

22:27.813 --> 22:31.750
if I was so much
more than that?

22:34.986 --> 22:37.022
Get ready for the end
of the world, Luke.

22:37.089 --> 22:39.758
An eternal sleep
of nightmares.

22:40.459 --> 22:41.793
Oh!

22:41.860 --> 22:43.729
And it's all your fault!

22:43.795 --> 22:45.397
(MANIACAL LAUGHING)

22:58.009 --> 23:00.412
RANI: Here's to Luke's
last night on Bannerman Road!

23:00.479 --> 23:02.481
-(LAUGHING)
-BOTH: Cheers.

23:02.547 --> 23:05.984
Cheers, Luke.
You all right, mate?

23:06.051 --> 23:08.286
-You'd tell us if there was
something wrong, yeah?
-Yeah.

23:08.353 --> 23:10.322
-Of course.
-He's gonna be fine.
This time tomorrow

23:10.388 --> 23:13.825
he's going to be in a
brand-new, exciting place.

23:13.892 --> 23:16.027
-(RANI LAUGHING)
-Come on, my turn.

23:16.094 --> 23:17.929
-Oh.
-Move over.

23:17.996 --> 23:21.199
-CLYDE: Come on, Rani.
-Come on.
Cheesy grin for Mum, please.

23:21.266 --> 23:23.068
<i>He'll forget about us,</i>
<i>I'm telling you.</i>

23:24.302 --> 23:25.537
Oh, it's lovely.

23:26.171 --> 23:27.539
(LAUGHING)

23:27.606 --> 23:28.874
(SNORING)

23:35.847 --> 23:37.415
He's such a lightweight.

23:41.019 --> 23:42.053
(SIGHS)

23:43.421 --> 23:45.857
-Don't go to sleep. Please.
-I'm not.

23:47.292 --> 23:48.827
I'm just tired.

23:58.036 --> 23:59.771
THE NIGHTMARE MAN: <i>You can't</i>
<i>say my name,</i>

23:59.838 --> 24:03.708
<i>you can't tell</i>
<i>anyone about me.</i>

24:08.780 --> 24:12.417
I'm supposed to be going
out there and living my life.

24:13.552 --> 24:14.820
It's not going to happen.

24:16.822 --> 24:19.491
The world's going to end,
and it's my fault.

24:22.194 --> 24:24.796
Because he's coming for me,
you see?

24:24.863 --> 24:26.665
He's been waiting
for me for years,

24:26.731 --> 24:28.700
and this week, he...

24:28.767 --> 24:30.068
(THE NIGHTMARE MAN LAUGHING)

24:32.704 --> 24:33.872
I can hear him.

24:36.208 --> 24:37.909
He's coming, so...

24:37.976 --> 24:41.179
<i>If you're watching,</i>
<i>just keep watching, because...</i>

24:41.246 --> 24:43.648
THE NIGHTMARE MAN: <i>Lukey boy!</i>

24:45.951 --> 24:47.919
<i>He's The Nightmare Man,</i>

24:47.986 --> 24:49.487
<i>and I can't stop him.</i>

24:50.088 --> 24:51.857
<i>Mum, I'm sorry.</i>

24:53.992 --> 24:57.929
That's why I'm trying now
so hard to stay awake.

24:58.129 --> 25:00.432
THE NIGHTMARE MAN:
<i>But you can't.</i>

25:00.498 --> 25:02.634
<i>I'm coming, Luke.</i>

25:03.468 --> 25:05.770
<i># It's time</i>

25:05.837 --> 25:08.306
<i># Go to sleep... #</i>

25:08.373 --> 25:09.407
No.

25:14.446 --> 25:16.648
<i>Sweet dreams!</i>

25:17.916 --> 25:20.652
(SUSPENSEFUL INSTRUMENTAL
MUSIC)

25:39.571 --> 25:40.705
I'm real!

25:41.339 --> 25:42.607
I'm here.

25:44.943 --> 25:47.712
And I'm real!

25:53.785 --> 25:55.787
No!

25:55.854 --> 25:58.857
(ECHOING)
Please! Can anyone hear me?

26:00.725 --> 26:01.860
Let me out!

26:02.994 --> 26:03.862
Let me out!

26:05.463 --> 26:06.564
Mum!

26:06.631 --> 26:07.866
Where am I?

26:08.934 --> 26:09.868
No!

26:11.937 --> 26:13.505
I'm going to stop you!

26:21.146 --> 26:24.983
MR SMITH: <i>Luke's Nightmare Man</i>
<i>is a Vishclar</i>
<i>from the Saretti dimension.</i>

26:25.050 --> 26:27.018
It's not real,
it's just a nightmare!

26:28.186 --> 26:30.989
I always knew
you were a stupid boy.

26:31.056 --> 26:32.390
Sarah Jane?

26:32.457 --> 26:34.759
I shouldn't be here!
I don't know what I'm doing.

26:34.826 --> 26:37.128
You are a journalist,
aren't you?

26:37.195 --> 26:40.498
My sensors indicate
Master Luke is asleep.

26:40.565 --> 26:42.867
He didn't record that video
because he was scared
but because he knew

26:42.934 --> 26:44.836
we'd find it
and he knew we'd save him.

26:44.903 --> 26:47.706
<i>This is a dream</i>
<i>and that you need to wake up.</i>

26:47.772 --> 26:50.075
I know, K9. I've tried...

26:50.141 --> 26:51.009
But I can't.
